<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-02-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-02-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="102" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d102">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">422.11G93/1008</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ecuadoran Minister</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Elizalde</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-05"><hi rend="italic">February 5,
                                        1919</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 3</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to your kind note No. 44 of
                                January 10 last,<note n="10" xml:id="d102fn10"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_172">p. 172</ref>.</note> I
                                have the honor to confirm my note No. 1 of the 9th of that
                                    month<note n="11" xml:id="d102fn11"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>,
                                        <ref target="#pg_171">p. 171</ref>.</note> and to inform you
                                that I received today from my Government a telegram that a final
                                remittance of 35000 pounds has paid in full the interests [<hi rend="italic">coupon of interest</hi>] of the Guayaquil and
                                Quito Railway Company for the year 1918.</p>
                            <p>My Government has thus redeemed the promise made to the Department of
                                State to effect the payment on condition that it would receive
                                permission to import 14000 tons of cocoa into the United States.</p>
                            <p>I avail myself [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">R. H.
                                Elizalde</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>